librope
------------------------------------------
This is a little C library for heavyweight utf-8 strings (rope). Unlike
regular C strings, ropes can do substring insertion and deletion in O(log n)
time.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.5-1
  librope-devel-1.0.0-1bl2
  librope1-1.0.0-1bl2
  pkg-config-2.5.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.45.1-1
  cmake-3.31.3-1
  cygport-0.37.3-1
  gcc-core-13.4.0-1
  ninja-1.13.1-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/josephg/librope

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/josephg/librope/archive/refs/tags/v1.0.0.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack librope-1.0.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./librope-1.0.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/librope-1.0.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/librope-1.0.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/librope1-1.0.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/librope-devel-1.0.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(librope)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/librope.README
  /usr/share/doc/librope/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/librope/README.md

(librope1)
  /usr/bin/cygrope-1.dll

(librope-devel)
  /usr/include/rope.h
  /usr/lib/librope.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/librope.pc

------------------

